 Boston designated hitter Andre Dawson had surgery to repair torn cartilage in 
his left knee and is expected to be sidelined about three to four weeks.Team 
physician Arthur Pappas said he repaired cartilage on the inside and outside of 
the knee and that the operation at the University of Massachusetts Medical 
Center in Worcester went well. It was the 10th time Dawson, 39, has had knee 
surgery. Dawson's knee locked up while he was running out a grounder Tuesday 
night against Cleveland. . . . Colorado pitcher Armando Reynoso had elbow 
