<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP; BRENTWOOD OUSTS BURBANK IN TENNIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Second-seeded Burbank High was stymied Thursday in its attempt to repeat as 
the Southern Section Division III boys' tennis champion, dropping a semifinal 
match on the road to third-seeded Brentwood, 12-9. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bulldogs (20-3) won only one set in singles play, a 6-2 victory by Vazghen 
Zaghiyian over Kevin Pivnick. 
</P>
<P>
 Burbank Coach Clyde Richards said the turning point came when the No. 1 
doubles team of Phil Cano and Brad Warner -- who are competing in today's 
individual quarterfinals -- lost, 6-4, to Brentwood's No. 1 team of Scott 
Kaufman and Tyler Barnett. 
</P>
<P>
 This marked Burbank's seventh consecutive year of reaching at least the 
quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
 Brentwood (17-3) will face Pasadena Poly in the team finals Wednesday. 
SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Pacifica 2, Newbury Park 0 -- Pinch-runner Melissa Bunim scored on a wild 
pitch and Amy Smith had an RBI single in a two-run sixth inning as 
fourth-seeded Pacifica (21-5-1) advanced to play Marina in the Division I 
semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon 9, Hesperia 2 -- The host Cowboys won a Division II quarterfinal. 
Canyon (19-5-1) will face Bishop Amat in the semifinals on Tuesday at a site to 
be determined. 
</P>
<P>
 South Hills 6, Quartz Hill 5 -- The Rebels (18-8) led, 3-2, and were tied, 
5-5, but could not overcome seven walks in a Division III quarterfinal. Cindy 
Sims had three hits, including a triple, and drove in a run. 
</P>
<P>
 Paraclete 10, Rancho Verde 0 -- Jamie Johnson recorded her 11th shutout -- a 
two-hitter striking out 10 and walking two -- as host Paraclete (23-5) advanced 
to the Division V semifinals. The senior helped her own cause with a three-run 
double in the sixth inning. 
</P>
<P>
 Ashley Gayre and Kristal Nessa contributed identical three-for-three, one-RBI 
performances. 
</P>
<P>
 Crossroads 1, Oak Park 0 -- Jessica Schulman took a no-hitter into the seventh 
inning, but finished with a one-hitter, leading the host Roadrunners (23-6) in 
a Division V quarterfinal game. Schulman struck out nine and walked one. 
Crossroads scored its only run on throwing error. 
</P>
<P>
 St. Lucy's 8, Alemany 5 -- The Indians (22-3) gave up four runs in the bottom 
of the sixth and lost a Division III quarterfinal game at St. Lucy's. Tammy 
Alcantar and Jamie Moore had two hits each for Alemany. 
</P>
<P>
 Templeton 10, Oakwood 0 -- Visiting Oakwood (16-4) was eliminated in a 
Division VI quarterfinal game. 
</P>
<P>
 Hesperia Christian 17, L.A. Lutheran 6 -- The visiting Lions (14-6) lost a 
Division VI quarterfinal game. 
</P>
<P>
 Boron 4, Antelope Valley Christian 0 -- The visiting Eagles' season ended in 
the Division VI quarterfinals. 
</P>
