<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CAMARILLO; MISSING HOSPITAL PATIENT IS FOUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 He was scratched up and hungry, but Camarillo State Hospital patient Scott 
Tipton was otherwise unharmed after spending four days wandering in the farm 
fields of Camarillo, hospital officials said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Tipton, who is deaf and has a limited ability to communicate, left the 
hospital grounds Sunday night and was apparently lost in the hills and farm 
fields until he pounded on the door of a house three miles from the hospital, 
according to a Ventura County Sheriff's Department spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
 The homeowner called the Sheriff's Department about 1:30 p.m. Thursday and the 
responding deputies recognized Tipton from photos that were distributed by the 
hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're very fortunate to have found him," said Myron Dimmett, a hospital 
spokesman. "He appears to be OK. When we found him he indicated that he was 
very hungry and wanted some candy." 
</P>
<P>
 Dimmett said he did not know where Tipton had been during the days he was 
missing, but he assumed that he had been wandering in the rugged area between 
the hospital and Pancho Road, where he was found. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're just glad he's back safely," Dimmett said. MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</TEXT>
