<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; CITY TO HOLD EVENT FOR SPRING 
CLEANERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEPHANIE SIMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Spring cleaners will get a chance to dump their garbage and yard waste at 
Thousand Oaks' annual Community Clean-up and Recycling Day, set for Saturday in 
Conejo Creek Park. 
</P>
<P>
 City officials expect at least 1,500 cars to stream through the park at the 
corner of Janss Road and the Moorpark Freeway from 8 a.m. to 3 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The city will not accept hazardous waste, but residents can bring old 
appliances, furniture, grass clippings, scrap metal, clothing or any other kind 
of household junk.Goodwill Industries representatives will be on hand to 
collect salvageable items. 
</P>
<P>
 Participants must be prepared to unload their own cars, and should expect to 
wait up to half an hour to enter the park. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is the largest event of its kind in Ventura County," recycling 
coordinator Grahame Watts said, "and it's always well-received." STEPHANIE 
SIMON 
