<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; WOMAN'S DEATH DECLARED HOMICIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After declaring that the death of a 33-year-old woman from a mysterious 
explosion here last week was a homicide and not an accident, Los Angeles County 
sheriff's deputies Thursday asked for the public's help in solving the case. 
</P>
<P>
 Lynn Standish of Pearblossom died, and her 4-year-old son, Michael Hepburn, 
was seriously injured May 20, when something exploded as they looked for 
collectibles and recyclables in the desert near 106th Street East and Avenue V. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators "have determined that it was a homicide and not an accident," 
Sgt. Ron Spear said. But investigators did not say how they had reached that 
conclusion, Spear said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
