<HEADLINE>
<P>
STREISAND'S 4 CANCELED SHOWS NOW SET FOR JULY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE HOCHMAN, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thursday will now be opening night for Barbra Streisand's celebrated Anaheim 
Pond concert engagement, and four shows postponed this week have been 
rescheduled to July, the singer's manager announced. 
</P>
<P>
 The engagement will pick up as scheduled with the Thursday performance and one 
June 4 in Anaheim, and Streisand will return to the Pond after engagements in 
San Jose and New York next month to make up the missed performances, said Marty 
Erlichman, her manager. 
</P>
<P>
 "I feel terrible that these postponements may cause severe scheduling problems 
for so many of my fans who have waited for so long for me to perform live," 
Streisand, who has suffered from viral tracheolaryngitis for nearly a week, 
said in a written statement released late Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Many fans had flown to Southern California from across the country 
specifically for the Streisand concerts, which had been scheduled to begin last 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Though Streisand had hoped to be well enough to begin the Anaheim shows 
tonight, Erlichman announced that the singer's doctors advised her to postpone 
tonight's show as well as scheduled appearances Sunday and Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets for the four postponed shows will be honored on July 18, 20, 22 and 
24. 
</P>
<P>
 If needed, refunds for the postponed shows will be made at points of purchase 
beginning Tuesday for full face value and Ticketmaster's service fee, officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The change of dates means that Streisand's tour -- her first in nearly three 
decades and, she says, her last -- presumably will end at the Pond. The 
notoriously stage-shy performer had been scheduled to end the six-city tour at 
New York's Madison Square Garden in June. 
</P>
<P>
 Speculation had been that any postponed shows would be made up between planned 
June 7 and 9 shows in San Jose and the start of Streisand's run at New York's 
Madison Square Garden beginning June 20. 
</P>
<P>
 But when it became necessary to move four Anaheim shows, that became 
impossible because of Streisand's refusal to perform on consecutive nights and 
because of the time needed to take her elaborate stage sets across the country. 
</P>
