<P>
U.S., VIETNAM TO OPEN LIAISON OFFICES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Building on President Clinton's lifting of the U.S. trade embargo, Vietnam and 
the United States announced an agreement Thursday for opening diplomatic 
missions in each other's capital. 
</P>
<P>
 The two nations will not exchange ambassadors, but the opening of liaison 
offices is "an important step toward normalization of relations," the 
Vietnamese Foreign Ministry said. 
</P>
<P>
 In Washington, White House press secretary Dee Dee Myers said, "It's the 
furtherance of a step the President announced when he lifted the trade 
embargo." 
</P>
