<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; ARSON FIRE 
SWEEPS THROUGH VACANT APARTMENT BUILDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fire swept through the top floor of a vacant, four-story apartment building in 
Hollywood on Thursday afternoon, jamming homebound commuter traffic throughout 
the area. 
</P>
<P>
 About 100 firefighters responded to the blaze that broke out about 5 p.m. in 
the building at 1720 N. Taft Avenue. The fire was controlled in about 40 
minutes and officials said that it had been set. They said the building was 
vacant because of damage suffered in the January earthquake. There were no 
reports of injuries. 
</P>
<P>
 Earlier Thursday, fire damaged part of another vacant apartment building about 
10 blocks away, at 5523 Lexington Avenue. Four firefighters received minor 
injuries battling that blaze. The causes of both fires were under 
investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
