<TEXT>
<P>
 Digital Equipment Corp. Names New CFO: The company, in an effort to accelerate 
its cost-cutting effort, named Vincent J. Mullarkey chief financial officer, 
effective immediately.Mullarkey, 46, formerly controller, replaces William M. 
Steul, 51, who resigned to pursue other interests, the Maynard, Mass., company 
said. Mullarkey retains the title of vice president. The corporate controller's 
position has not been filled yet. The nation's No. 2 computer maker has posted 
losses for the past three years. It has come under even more pressure to get 
its financial house in order after posting a loss for the third quarter ended 
April 3 that was four times deeper than analysts had expected. 
</P>
