</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 China Allows Foreign Investment in Airlines: The country has opened its 
airlines and airports to foreign investment in a bid to upgrade its badly 
strained air transport infrastructure, the China Daily reported today.Foreign 
carriers will now be allowed to invest in Chinese airlines or launch joint and 
cooperative projects, such as the setting up of new airlines, the newspaper 
said. However, under Civil Aviation Administration of China rules, foreign 
investment in a joint-venture airline will be limited to 35%, and foreign 
voting rights will be capped at 25%. This year, China vowed to overhaul its air 
transport industry, which has groaned under the weight of double-digit growth 
in demand. 
</P>
