<P>
 New Jobless Claims Dip Slightly: The number of Americans filing new claims for 
state unemployment benefits fell slightly last week for the second consecutive 
week, the Labor Department said.Claims fell to 366,000 in the week ended May 21 
from 367,000 the previous week, above Wall Street economists' forecasts of 
361,000. The department's closely watched four-week moving average, which is 
considered a more accurate indicator of jobless trends, posted a gain. The 
average climbed to 366,750 last week, up from a revised 359,250 in the week 
ended May 14. The department said the last time the average was that high was 
in the week ended Feb. 19, when it stood at 375,000. 
