<TEXT>
<P>
 Money Supply Mixed: The Federal Reserve Board said the measure known as M2 
rose to a seasonally adjusted $3,590.8 billion in the week ended May 16, from a 
revised $3,587.9 billion the previous week.An even broader measure, M3, fell to 
a seasonally adjusted $4,214.3 billion from a revised $4,214.4 billion. The 
narrowest measure of the money supply, M1, rose to a seasonally adjusted 
$1,143.5 billion from $1,142.5 billion. M1 includes cash in circulation, 
deposits in checking accounts and non-bank traveler's checks. M2 is M1 plus 
accounts such as savings deposits and money market mutual funds. M3 is M2 plus 
less-liquid accounts, such as certificates of deposit in minimum denominations 
of $100,000. 
</P>
