</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Music: EastWest Records and the best-selling West Coast rap group Da Lench Mob 
are parting ways in the wake of murder charges being filed against two of the 
group's members. EastWest is part of Time Warner's Atlantic Group.Da Lench 
Mob's "Guerillas in tha Mist" was one of the top-selling rap albums nationally 
in 1992 and 1993. In a brief statement, EastWest Chairman and Chief Executive 
Sylvia Rhone said, "It would be in the best interest of both parties to 
discontinue our relationship." Sources within the company attributed the action 
to the group's legal problems as well as creative differences. A lawyer for the 
group's production company said a mutual release was agreed upon. . . . Moving 
Target Productions, the production company of former Paramount Pictures chief 
Brandon Tartikoff, has linked up with former Warner Bros. executive Michael Jay 
Solomon's international sales company on a three-year distribution agreement, 
starting with the international rights to the television movie "XXX's and 
OOO's." JAMES BATES 
