<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE GOODS; THE DISCOUNT YEARS; AS WE GET OLDER, MANY OF THE PLEASURES IN LIFE 
GET CHEAPER. AND, THANK GOODNESS, SO DO SOME OF THE NECESSITIES. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GARY LIBMAN, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Most people want to be younger. 
</P>
<P>
 But if that's not working, if aches and wrinkles seem to be gaining on you, 
consider the advantages of getting older. 
</P>
<P>
 The number of discounts offered to "mature" audiences has expanded vastly in 
recent years. 
</P>
<P>
 Once, a mere trickle of price reductions were available for people over 65. 
Today, the trickle has turned into a torrent and benefits people as young as 
50, says an author of a book on senior discounts. 
</P>
<P>
 Discounts are expanding as more businesses recognize that people over 50 are 
America's fastest-growing population segment and control half the discretionary 
income, says Joan Rattner Heilman, author of "Unbelievably Good Deals & Great 
Adventures That You Absolutely Can't Get Unless You're Over 50" (Contemporary 
Books, 1994). 
</P>
<P>
 Here are a few of the bargains available. Many other places also offer 
discounts so, if you have reached 50, don't be shy about asking. Entertainment 
& Attractions 
</P>
<P>
 Ahmanson at the Doolittle -- $41, $45 and $49 theater tickets half price, 
subject to availability, one hour before all performances. Must have picture ID 
and pay cash. Minimum age: 65. (213) 972-0700. 
</P>
<P>
 Descanso Gardens -- $5 admission reduced to $3. Minimum age: 62. (818) 
952-4400. 
</P>
<P>
 Disneyland -- $31 admission reduced to $25. Minimum age: 60. (714) 999-4565. 
</P>
<P>
 Hollywood Bowl -- Two tickets priced as high as $19.50 may be purchased for $6 
each, starting one day before Tuesday, Wednesday or Thursday performances. 
Subject to availability. Must have Medicare card, driver's license, RTD bus 
pass or birth certificate for ID. Minimum age: 63. (213) 850-2000. 
</P>
<P>
 Knott's Berry Farm -- $26.95 admission reduced to $17.95. Minimum age: 60. 
(714) 220-5220. 
</P>
<P>
 L.A. County Museum of Art -- $6 admission reduced to $4. Minimum age: 62. 
(213) 857-6000. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles Philharmonic concerts at Dorothy Chandler Pavilion at the Music 
Center -- Tickets priced from $9.50 to $50 may be purchased for $6 up to two 
weeks before Wednesday evening and Friday matinee performances. Subject to 
availability. Limit one ticket per ID. Minimum age: 62. Seniors also get 50% 
discounts on some subscriptions. Two per ID. Minimum age: 63. (213) 850-2000. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles Zoo -- $8 admission reduced to $5. Minimum age: 60. (213) 
666-4090. 
</P>
<P>
 Magic Mountain -- $29 admission reduced to $18. Minimum age: 55. Proof of age 
required. (805) 255-4111. 
</P>
<P>
 Mark Taper Forum -- $28-$35 tickets available for half price, subject to 
availability, on day of performance only. (Saturday nights not included.) Must 
have Medicare card to prove age and must pay cash. Minimum age: 62. (213) 
972-0700. 
</P>
<P>
 Museum of Tolerance -- $7.50 admission reduced to $5.50. Minimum age: 62. 
(310) 553-8403. 
</P>
<P>
 Richard Nixon Library & Birthplace -- $4.95 admission reduced to $2.95. 
Minimum age: 62. (Everyone free through May 31.) (714) 993-3393. 
</P>
<P>
 Universal Studios Hollywood -- $29.95 admission reduced to $23.95. Minimum 
age: 60. (818) 508-9600. 
</P>
<P>
 Health Care 
</P>
<P>
 Cedars-Sinai Medical Center -- Free senior care program offers 10%-30% 
discount from participating providers of home health care and on orthopedic 
supplies not covered by Medicare. The program also offers discounts from 
providers of prescriptions and glasses and offers free health lectures, health 
insurance counseling, and an information and referral hot line. The fee for an 
aerobic exercise class is discounted. Minimum age: 65. (310) 855-5454. 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale Memorial Hospital and Health Center -- 10%-20% discounts from 
participating pharmacies, suppliers of hearing aids, glasses and on some eye 
exams. Also 5%-20% reduction from participating providers of home health care 
services. Free screenings for blood pressure and prostate problems, free 
participation in Walk-a-Diles Walking Club and other exercise classes, and free 
assistance with Medicare and other insurance problems. Minimum age: 50. 
Provides $8 mature-driving class, which leads to discounts in auto insurance. 
Minimum age: 55. (818) 502-2396. ((818) 502-2380 for cancer screenings.) 
</P>
<P>
 Lens Crafters -- 10% discount on glasses, frames and accessories. Will fill 
out Medicare forms for patients who have had cataract surgery. If a doctor 
changes a prescription during the six months following cataract surgery, the 
company will replace the patient's lenses at no charge. Minimum age: 65. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Monica Hospital -- 10%-20% discounts through providers of glasses, 
prescription drugs, hearing aids and home health services. Discounted exercise 
programs, Medic Alert bracelets and Wednesday evening mammograms. Also free 
health lectures, walking program, blood pressure screenings twice a month, and 
eye, ear and skin screenings at different times. Minimum age: 50. Provides $8 
mature-driving class, which leads to discounts in car insurance. Minimum age: 
55. (310) 319-4560. 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California College of Optometry -- 10% discount on glasses but not on 
contact lenses. Free cataract and glaucoma screening Monday and Friday 
mornings. Call for appointment. Minimum age: 62. (714) 449-7400. 
</P>
<P>
 YMCA -- Membership discounts of $5-$10 a month at most branches. Minimum age: 
check with branch. 
</P>
<P>
 Sports 
</P>
<P>
 Hollywood Park -- $6 general admission tickets for $4 on Thursdays through 
July 21. Includes parking and program. Minimum age: 62. (310) 419-1500. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles Dodgers -- $6 tickets in top deck or outfield pavilion for $3 for 
all day games, subject to availability. Sales begin 90 minutes before game. 
Minimum age: 55. (213) 224-1500. 
</P>
<P>
 Movies 
</P>
<P>
 AMC -- 50% discount on most tickets. Minimum age: 55. 
</P>
<P>
 Edwards -- $6.50 and $6.75 tickets are reduced to $3.50 and $3.75. Minimum 
age: 55. 
</P>
<P>
 Mann -- $4 tickets for all shows except premieres. Minimum age: 60. 
</P>
<P>
 Travel 
</P>
<P>
 American Assn. of Retired Persons -- for $8 membership fee, offers 5%-10% 
discounts for three rental car companies and discounts as high as 50% at 22 
hotel chains, including Best Western, Holiday Inn and Sheraton Resorts. Also 
reductions on some tours and cruises. (310) 496-2277. 
</P>
<P>
 Amtrak -- 15% discount on any coach-class ticket. Some exceptions apply. 
Minimum age: 62. 
</P>
<P>
 Gray Line Worldwide -- 15% off fares for some half- or full-day sightseeing 
tours at participating Gray Line locations in the United States and Canada. 
Minimum age: 50 (with AARP membership card). 
</P>
<P>
 Airlines 
</P>
<P>
 American, Delta, United and some other airlines offer booklets of four coupons 
for $596 or eight for $1,032. One coupon is required each way on trips within 
the continental United States and two coupons are needed each way on flights 
from continental U.S. to Hawaii or Alaska. Reservations must be made 14 days in 
advance and there may be restrictions. Minimum age: 62. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition: 
</P>
<P>
 American Airlines -- 10% discount on any fare, subject to restrictions. 
Minimum age: 62. 
</P>
<P>
 Delta Airlines -- 10% off published fares to any Delta destination in North 
America or the Caribbean. Some promotional fares excluded. Some discounts are 
available for international travel but reductions vary. Minimum age: 62. 
</P>
<P>
 Southwest Airlines -- 10% discount off lowest available fare. Limited seats on 
every flight. Must make reservations at least one day in advance and present 
proof of age. Minimum age: 65. 
</P>
<P>
 United Airlines -- 10% discount off any published fare. Must meet advance 
purchase requirements, if any, on each fare. Minimum age: 62. 
</P>
<P>
 Car Rentals 
</P>
<P>
 Avis -- Discounts to AARP members. Savings vary with location, destination, 
time of year. Minimum age: 50. 
</P>
<P>
 Enterprise -- 10% discount for AARP members. Minimum age: 50. 
</P>
<P>
 Hertz -- Discounts for members of AARP, the National Assn. of Retired Federal 
Employees and retired military officers. Discount and minimum age vary. 
</P>
<P>
 Odds & Ends 
</P>
<P>
 Backroads -- Biking, walking and hiking trips, and cross-country skiing, 
running and multisport programs. Trips are open to people of all ages, but 
senior discounts begin at age 60. Each trip has varied daily mileage options 
and is accompanied by a van, so people of different abilities can take part. 
Trips are offered in 20 countries and in 20 states. Closest to Los Angeles are 
five- and six-day biking trips in Big Sur. (800) 462-2848. 
</P>
<P>
 First Interstate Bank -- Free checking. Minimum age: 55. 
</P>
<P>
 Golf Card -- Chance to play free twice a year at each of more than 2,500 golf 
courses, mostly rural ones in the Midwest and Northeast. Must call 24 hours in 
advance and rent a powered cart. $95 a year for single membership; $145 for 
double. Minimum age: none, but average age of members is 61. (800) 321-8269. 
</P>
<P>
 Hughes Markets -- 5% discount on almost all items at 51 stores in five 
Southern California counties. Minimum age: 65. 
</P>
<P>
 Quinn's Health Pantry -- two Hollywood health-food stores offer a 5% discount 
on everything except advertised specials. Minimum age: 55. (213) 663-8307 or 
(213) 651-5950. 
</P>
<P>
 Ross Dress for Less -- 10% discount on all items every Tuesday at 50 stores in 
Los Angeles area. Minimum age: 55. 
</P>
<P>
 70+ Ski Club -- 10-page list of free or discounted downhill skiing sites in 
the United States, Australia, New England, France and Switzerland. Proof of age 
and $5 fee required. Minimum age: 70. Write for information: 104 Eastside 
Drive, Ballston Lake, N.Y. 12019. 
</P>
<P>
 UCLA Extension -- 50% fee reduction for many classes. To assure a place, 
students should pre-enroll in person or by mail. Must present proof of age. 
Courses are taught primarily on UCLA campus, Downtown at World Trade Center and 
at Universal CityWalk. Minimum age: 65. (310) 206-6201. 
</P>
