<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXHIBITION TO HONOR ARTIST WESTMORELAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An exhibition honoring artist La Monte Westmoreland, whose home and art 
collection were destroyed in the 1993 Altadena fire, opens June 19 at the Jose 
Drudis-Biada Art Gallery at Mount St. Mary's College. 
</P>
<P>
 Westmoreland, the longtime director of Santa Monica High School's Roberts 
Gallery, lost hundreds of pieces in the fire, but artists are helping him to 
rebuild his collection. 
</P>
<P>
 Donated works by 37 artists, including Craig Antrim, Laddie John Dill and Kent 
Twitchell will be on view. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (310) 476-2237. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA052794-0269 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 045920 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
