</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WILLSON CUMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Some good news for residents and commuters in Santa Ana: Temporary ramps are 
scheduled to open today to allow motorists to exit and enter the southbound 
Santa Ana Freeway at Grand Avenue.  
</P>
<P>
 Access to busy Grand Avenue has been disrupted since the southbound off-ramp 
closed in December, Caltrans spokeswoman Maureena Duran-Rojas said.The ramp to 
get on the southbound Santa Ana Freeway from Grand Avenue closed in March, 
Duran-Rojas said. 
</P>
<P>
 The temporary ramps will remain open until construction of the permanent ramps 
is finished in late 1995, Duran-Rojas said. Both temporary ramps are scheduled 
to open this morning, but perhaps not in time for the morning rush hour, 
Duran-Rojas said. 
</P>
<P>
 The northbound on-ramp at Grand Avenue is now open only to drivers heading 
north on the street. The ramp to Grand Avenue from the northbound Santa Ana 
Freeway is still closed, though it may open this summer, according to Caltrans. 
WILLSON CUMMER 
