<TEXT>
<P>
 New Union Pacific President Named: Richard Davidson, chairman of the Union 
Pacific Railroad, was elected president of parent company Union Pacific Corp. 
Davidson, 52, was also named a director of the corporation, as were L. White 
Matthews III, 49, its executive vice president for finance, and Jack Messman, 
54, chief executive of Union Pacific Resources, the oil and gas subsidiary.All 
three men will continue to report to Drew Lewis, chairman of Union Pacific 
Corp. Davidson has been chairman of the railroad since September, 1991. 
Bethlehem, Pa.-based Union Pacific Corp. runs the nation's third-largest 
railroad. It also owns gas and oil wells and a trucking firm. 
